name: Vauxhall Cavalier  Mk I print
description:
In his debut series for imagesurgery, artist Joel Harrison expresses his nostalgic appreciation for everyday motors of the 1970s and 80s. Joel was intrigued by how the cars in these images appear strikingly cool, despite being considered the mundane workhorses of their day. Inspiration also came from Robert Bechtle’s paintings of 1960s and 70s American suburbia - many of which celebrate people's cars and home environment. But the setting for Joel’s carefully drafted illustrations include telltale details - lampposts, pillar boxes and vernacular architecture - that make them unmistakably British.

Vauxhall Cavalier Mk I (1975–81)


This is one of a series of four designs, digitally composed and then hand-finished as vector artwork. Perfectly reproduced as a high-resolution giclée at A1 size (594 x 841mm), it's printed on photo-rag paper for a crisp, flat, matt finish. We have been especially pleased with the quality of these prints, which use lightfast inks and archival paper to endure a lifetime without fading or discolouration. Each is limited to 30 editions. Delivery in the UK is free. The print will be rolled and shipped in a sturdy cardboard tube. To obtain overseas shipping quotes, add items to the cart and select your country from the menu. We can arrange mounting, framing and delivery at additional cost. For further information contact info@imagesurgery.com
